courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon the completion of this course, students should be able to:   
   
1. Apply their knowledge of cancer biology and related skills in real-life situations;    
2. Sharpen their problem-solving abilities;   
3. Strengthen their organizational power;    
4. Develop effective communicative and interpersonal skills through group work;   
5. Disseminate cancer-related information in a clear, concise and logical manner;   
6. Create innovative ideas and methods to solve problems in the cancer research field  
   
7. Appreciate the advantages of cooperative learning;    
8. Become an effective member in group dynamics; and   
   
9. Accept new challenges and independent responsibilities.
